attributeList.attribute: Required for the synthesis of Coenzyme Q (CoQ), an isoprenylated benzoquinone which functions as an electron carrier from complex I or II to complex III in the inner mitochondrial membrane and which also acts as an antioxidant preventing the oxidation of lipoproteins and the plasma membrane. Assembly of the complex appears to be triggered by 4-hydroxyl-3-hexaprenyl benzoate (HHB) which is a precursor of CoQ.

Complex assembly requires the post-translational modification of COQ proteins. Assembly starts with a nucleation around the HBB bound to a nucleating COQ protein, potentially COQ4. The nucleation step is ended with the assembly of a pre-complex that accumulates a CoQ6 intermediate, the demethoxy quinone (DMQ6). DMQ6 is converted to CoQ6 after the activation of COQ7 by dephosphorylation by PTC7. This event allows for the full assembly of the complex. Molecular weight = 1300kDa.
